{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, photonics serve electronics by providing the data links, and electronics serve photonics by providing control and readout and digital signal processing (DSP).",
    "A major difference between photonics and electronics is that photons don't interact and thus are excellent for transmission of information, whereas electrons interact and repel each other and thus make good switches and computing elements.",
    "Each silicon photonic switch therefore requires a corresponding electronic switch.",
    "On the whole, the number of transistors in the EIC that must accompany an LSI PIC are orders of magnitude larger than the number of components in the PIC.",
    "Here lies a natural interplay, since transistors consume much lower power in (1) switching, (2) providing gain (both linear and limiting), and (3) offering high precision, while being orders of magnitude smaller than the photonic components 124."
  ]
}